---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Scrabble Words from Electricity — High-Voltage Terms That Score"
  description="Electrical terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. VOLTAGE (11pts), WATTAGE (11pts), OHMS (9pts). Power up your game with electricity vocabulary."
  keywords="scrabble electricity words, voltage scrabble points, wattage scrabble, ohms scrabble, electrical terms scrabble, power words scrabble, circuit words scrabble"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Scrabble Words from Electricity — High-Voltage Terms That Score","description":"Electrical terms valid in Scrabble with full scoring. VOLTAGE (11pts), WATTAGE (11pts), OHMS (9pts).","datePublished":"2026-06-30","author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com","url":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"ScrabbleWordsFinder.com"},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/scrabble-words-from-electricity"}})} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is VOLTAGE a valid Scrabble word?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes! VOLTAGE scores 11 points (V=4, O=1, L=1, T=1, A=1, G=2, E=1). It's a 7-letter word making it a bingo candidate worth 61 points with the 50-point bonus."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can you play WATTAGE in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. WATTAGE scores 11 points (W=4, A=1, T=1, T=1, A=1, G=2, E=1). Another 7-letter bingo candidate from electrical vocabulary, valid in both TWL and SOWPODS."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What electrical words score highest in Scrabble?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"SPARKING scores 15 points, VOLTAGE and WATTAGE each score 11, and OHMS scores 9. Words with W=4, V=4, and K=5 tiles tend to score highest in this category."}}]})} />
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1"><a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a><span class="mx-1">›</span><span class="text-gray-300">Word Lists</span></nav>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Scrabble Words from Electricity — High-Voltage Terms That Score</h1>
      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400"><time datetime="2026-06-30">June 30, 2026</time><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><span>5 min read</span><span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span><a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a></div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy for Electrical Words</h2>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">VOLTAGE and WATTAGE are natural bingos:</span> Both are exactly 7 letters. If you see V-O-L-T-A-G-E or W-A-T-T-A-G-E on your rack, play them immediately for 11 base + 50 bonus = 61 points.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">OHMS is a 4-letter power play:</span> At 9 points from just 4 tiles, OHMS gives 2.25 points per tile — excellent efficiency. The H=4 does the heavy lifting.</p></div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors"><p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Hook with S plurals:</span> VOLTS, WATTS, FUSES, OHMS — all take S naturally, making them easy parallel plays beside existing words.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Key Insight</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">Electrical words are <span class="text-white font-medium">V-tile and W-tile specialists</span>. Both tiles are worth 4 points, and electricity vocabulary uses them heavily — VOLTAGE, VOLTS, WATTAGE, WATTS, WIRED. When you draw V or W, think electrical.</p>
      </div>
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-800 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-science/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Science</span></a>
          <a href="/blog/scrabble-words-from-technology/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group"><span class="text-blue-500 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span><span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Scrabble Words from Technology</span></a>
        </div>
      </aside>
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-cyan-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Find every valid electrical word instantly — free Scrabble solver, no sign-up</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center"><a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a></div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
